<title>USA: Illinois direct hogs unevenly steady - USDA.</title>
<headline>Illinois direct hogs unevenly steady - USDA.</headline>
<dateline>SPRINGFIELD 1997-01-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>USDA said barrows and gilts were unevenly steady. Demand was moderate on light offerings. Top $53.50 per cwt.</p>
<p>US 1-2 230-260 lbs. 51.50-53.00, mostly 52.00-53.00, few 53.50.</p>
<p>Sows - mostly steady. Top $49.00.</p>
<p>US 1-3 300-450 lbs. 40.00-43.00</p>
<p>	     450-500 lbs. 43.00-45.00</p>
<p>	     500-600 lbs. 45.00-47.00</p>
<p>	     few over 600 lbs. 47.00-49 00</p>
</text>
